attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.
text: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something; a trial.

exampleUses.text: a test of one's eyesight; subjecting a hypothesis to a test; a test of an athlete's endurance.

attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.
text: A series of questions, problems, or physical responses designed to determine knowledge, intelligence, or ability.

attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.
text: A basis for evaluation or judgment.

citations.cite: “A test of democratic government is how Congress and the president work together”
